{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Automatically install swiftly and Swift toolchains.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/SwiftlyDocs\/documentation\/SwiftlyDocs\/automated-install"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swiftly"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Install swiftly automatically"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This guide helps you to automate the installation of swiftly and toolchains so that it can run unattended, for example in build or continous integration systems.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This guide assumes that you have working understanding of your build system.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The examples are based on a typical Unix environment.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Download-the-binary",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Download the binary",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "First, download the swiftly binary from swift.org for your operating system (for example, Linux) and processor architecture (for example ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "arm64",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "x86_64",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Here’s an example using the popular curl command.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "curl -L https:\/\/download.swift.org\/swiftly\/linux\/swiftly-$(uname -m).tar.gz > swiftly.tar.gz",
            "tar zxf swiftly.tar.gz"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "On macOS, download the pkg file and extract it like this from the command-line:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "curl -L https:\/\/download.swift.org\/swiftly\/darwin\/swiftly.pkg > swiftly.pkg",
            "installer -pkg swiftly.pkg -target CurrentUserHomeDirectory"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "If you are using Linux you will need GPG and the “ca-certificates” package for the root certificate authorities that will establish the trust that swiftly needs to make API requests that it needs. This package is frequently pre-installed on end-user environments, but may not be present in more minimal installations.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Tip",
          "style" : "tip",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Install-swiftly",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Install swiftly",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Once swiftly is downloaded, run the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "init",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " subcommand to finish the installation.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following example command prints verbose outputs, assume yes for all prompts, and skips the automatic installation of the latest swift toolchain:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            ".\/swiftly init --verbose --assume-yes --skip-install    # the swiftly binary is extracted to ~\/local\/bin\/swiftly on macOS"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swiftly is installed, but the current shell may not yet be updated with the new environment variables, such as ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PATH",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "init",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command prints instructions on how to update the current shell environment without opening a new shell.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following output is an example from Linux, the details might be different for other OSes, username, or shell:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "To begin using installed swiftly from your current shell, first run the following command:",
            "",
            ". \"\/root\/.local\/share\/swiftly\/env.sh\""
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "On macOS, run ‘hash -r’ to recalculate the zsh PATH cache when installing swiftly and toolchains.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can go ahead and add this command to the list of commands in your build script so that the build can proceed to call swiftly from the path.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Install-a-toolchain",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Install a toolchain",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The usual next step is to install a specific swift toolchain using the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "install",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " command with the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--post-install-file",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " option:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swiftly install 5.10.1 --post-install-file=post-install.sh"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It’s possible that there will be some post-installation steps to prepare the system for using the swift toolchain.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If additional post-install steps are needed to use the toolchain they are written to the file you specified; ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "post-install.sh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the example above.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can check if the file exists and run it to perform those final steps.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If the build runs as the root user you can check it and run it like this in a typical Unix shell:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "if [ -f post-install.sh ]; then",
            "    . post-install.sh",
            "fi"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "If the system runs your script as a regular user then you will need to take this into account by either pre-installing the toolchain’s system dependencies or running the ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "post-install.sh",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " script in a secure manner as the administrative user.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Customize-the-installation",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Customize the installation",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you want to install swiftly, or the binaries that it manages into different locations these can be customized using environment variables before running ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly init",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "definition" : {
                "content" : [
                  {
                    "inlineContent" : [
                      {
                        "text" : "The location of the swiftly configuration files, and environment scripts",
                        "type" : "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type" : "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term" : {
                "inlineContent" : [
                  {
                    "code" : "SWIFTLY_HOME_DIR",
                    "type" : "codeVoice"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "definition" : {
                "content" : [
                  {
                    "inlineContent" : [
                      {
                        "text" : "The location of the swiftly binary and toolchain symbolic links (for example swift, swiftc, and so on)",
                        "type" : "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type" : "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term" : {
                "inlineContent" : [
                  {
                    "code" : "SWIFTLY_BIN_DIR",
                    "type" : "codeVoice"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "definition" : {
                "content" : [
                  {
                    "inlineContent" : [
                      {
                        "text" : "The temporary directory swiftly uses to hold large files, such as downloads, until it cleans them up.",
                        "type" : "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type" : "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term" : {
                "inlineContent" : [
                  {
                    "code" : "TMPDIR",
                    "type" : "codeVoice"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "type" : "termList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Sometimes swiftly can’t automatically detect the system platform, or isn’t supported by swift.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can provide the platform as an option to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly init",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " subcommand:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swiftly init --platform=<platform_name>"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "There are other customizable options, such as overwrite.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For more details about the available options, check the help:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swiftly init --help"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In summary, swiftly can be installed and install toolchains unattended on build and CI-style systems.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This guide has outlined the process to script the process covering some of the different options available to you.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
